  **DIDComm Present Proof Complete!**
  
  **Protocol Flow:**
  1. Verifier sends proof request (attributes + predicates)
  2. Holder receives via mediator (push notification)
  3. Holder finds matching credentials
  4. Holder selects credentials
  5. Holder generates ZK proofs (AnonCreds)
  6. Holder sends presentation
  7. Verifier validates proofs
  8. Verifier sends acknowledgment
  
  **Zero-Knowledge Proofs (ZKP):**
  ‚úì Predicates without revealing values
  ‚úì Selective disclosure (only requested attrs)
  ‚úì Unlinkability (can't correlate presentations)
  ‚úì Non-revocation proofs
  ‚úì Signature proofs
  
  **Privacy Features:**
  ‚úì Minimal disclosure (only what's needed)
  ‚úì Mathematical guarantees (not just promises)
  ‚úì No correlation between proofs
  ‚úì No tracking by verifiers
  
  **AnonCreds Advantages:**
  ‚úì True ZKP support (CL signatures)
  ‚úì Predicate proofs (age >= 18, salary > X)
  ‚úì Non-revocation proofs
  ‚úì Strong privacy guarantees
  ‚úì Production-ready (Hyperledger Indy)
  
  **Use Cases:**
  - Age verification (>= 18, >= 21)
  - Income verification (> threshold)
  - Date verification (employed before X)
  - Status checks (is_student = true)
  - All without revealing exact values!
end note

